The vertices of a $ 3 - 4 - 5$ right triangle are the centers of three mutually externally tangent circles, as shown. What is the sum of the areas of the three circles?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(5mm);
defaultpen(fontsize(10pt)+linewidth(.8pt));

pair B=(0,0), C=(5,0);
pair A=intersectionpoints(Circle(B,3),Circle(C,4))[0];

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(Circle(C,3));
draw(Circle(A,1));
draw(Circle(B,2));

label("$A$",A,N);
label("$B$",B,W);
label("$C$",C,E);
label("3",midpoint(B--A),NW);
label("4",midpoint(A--C),NE);
label("5",midpoint(B--C),S);
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A) } 12\pi\qquad \textbf{(B) } \frac {25\pi}{2}\qquad \textbf{(C) } 13\pi\qquad \textbf{(D) } \frac {27\pi}{2}\qquad \textbf{(E) } 14\pi$
